cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.LG

This paper deals with logical frameworks and formal specifications of programming languages and inference systems, which are topics typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the difficulties of formal meta-theoretic analysis, which is a topic covered in cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
